A community leader, rice merchant, Mrs. Ebhomen Theresa Agbator nee Airamoehi is dead. She died on March 2, 2022. She was 97 years old. The family has announced burial arrangements for the late mother, grandmother and great grandmother. The burial programme kick starts on May 19, 2022 with a Service of songs by 4pm at the Agbator family compound, 11/13 Ujoelen Road Ekpoma. Lying -in- State is at her compound, Ujoelen Road Ekpoma, May 20th 8 a.m. Thereafter, a funeral service will hold by 1pm at St. Andrews Anglican Cathedral Eguare Ekpoma. Interment follows immediately at her compound.   Pernod Ricard shines at Kantar awards     Onitsha: Dead city rising again     2023: Senatorial aspirant alleges harassment, cries to APC…   Social Dance and entertainment of guest holds the next day May 21st at the AAU Secondary School compound, Ihumuduma Road, Ekpoma while a Thanksgiving service in honour of Mama will hold May 22nd at St. Andrew’s Anglican Cathedral Ekpoma. Mama, fondly called Nene by everyone who knew her is survived by 7 children, 102 grand and great grandchildren. Among her children is Mrs. Lina Hayble. Mama, was a devout Anglican and a frontline community leader in Ekpoma Edo state. In her heydays she was one of the business women that dominated the rice and kola nut market in Nigeria.